<system_of_measurement wordnetid="113577171" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../172/3172.xml">
ANSI C</link></system_of_measurement>
</standard>
 (ANSI X3.159-1989) and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../497/607497.xml">
C99</link>, and provide several common extensions and dialects, including <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../013/6782013.xml">
MISRA C</link> diagnostics, <programming_language wordnetid="106898352" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../021/6021.xml#xpointer(//*[./st=%22K=26R_C%22])">
K&amp;R C</link></programming_language>
 (advertised as compatible with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../712/3712.xml">
Bell Labs</link>' original <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<communicator wordnetid="109610660" confidence="0.8">
